Show Moonlight current state:ph_check_app_name -s -a Moonlight | more
Start or switch to Moonlight:startmoon.sh | more
Stop Moonlight:stopmoon.sh force | more
Restart Moonlight:restartmoon.sh | more
Install Moonlight and integrate with PieHelper:confapps_ph.sh -p int -a Moonlight
Remove Moonlight from PieHelper and uninstall:confapps_ph.sh -p rem -a Moonlight
Configure Moonlight (set all required options and pair):confapps_ph.sh -p conf -a Moonlight
Update Moonlight to the latest version (only if installed as a package):ph_update_pkg $PH_MOON_PKG_NAME
List/Select shared game(s) for Moonlight streaming:listmoon_ph.sh
List all available options for Moonlight:confopts_ph.sh -p list -a Moonlight | more
View the value of any Moonlight option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Moonlight -g
View the value of any Moonlight option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Moonlight -g -r
View/Change the value of read-write Moonlight option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Moonlight -s
View/Change the value of read-write Moonlight option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Moonlight -s -r
Set all Moonlight options back to default:ph_set_all_options_to_default Moonlight
Display help for Moonlight option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Moonlight -d
Display help for Moonlight option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Moonlight -d -r
Display TTY currently allocated to Moonlight:confapps_ph.sh -p tty -a Moonlight | more
Move Moonlight to another TTY:confapps_ph.sh -p move -a Moonlight -t prompt
Go to Main menu:ph_show_menu Main
Go to Apps menu:ph_show_menu Apps
Open Shell to home directory (Type 'CTRL-D' to return):cd;/bin/bash
Return to previous screen:return
